title: 820-3476-a not turning on.
message:
Hi, 

Logic board was water damaged in U7501 area. Cleaned, replaced U7501 and R7537 C7537 C7536 that were burnt. Now seems that i am getting all reail ok but dont getting ALL SYS GOOD. 


CHecked and seems that board tries to enter S0 state once connect adapter. PP3V3_S0 is 1.7V and PP5V_S0 0 V.  As i see i will not get sys good while PP5V_S0 is not activated. 


Bad U7501 ??? ALready replaced it twice.

title: 820-3476-a not turning on.
message:
Post voltage on big coils.
Also check for short on all power rails which don't even pulse.

title: 820-3476-a not turning on.
message:

L7520, L7320/10, L3095 are 0V

title: 820-3476-a not turning on.
message:

Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check that.
Check all other coils at same moment.

"Now seems that i am getting all reail ok"
How that?
You've said to get only 3V3_S5; didn't say anything about pulse (at least) on other coils...
